title: For Sale:  PVS-14 Gen 3 Autogated Night Vision Monocular w/ accessories
postcontent: This is a PVS-14 Gen 3 night vision monocular in lightly used condition. It produces an exceptionally clear image with virtually no spots or blemishes, meaning it was probably hand selected for tube quality (it is within specs for even a new $3600 unit to have a few black spots around the edge of the image, which this one doesn't have). This unit appears to be autogated -- it dims when pointed at a bright light, which prevents tube damage. This unit comes with a dual battery housing, which gives it a longer battery life than the single battery units (65 hours continual use as opposed to 40 hours). It takes AA batteries.I was told by the previous owner that this unit has only been used for a few hours... the condition of the unit and quality of the image is definitely consistent with that. I have used it less than an hour myself, so it has the vast majority of its service life left, and will provide many good years of service.I was also told by the previous owner that this unit has an Omni tube, meaning it is mil spec and that unlike the ITT/Pinnacle tubes, it is rated for .308 recoil.It comes with the attached lens cover/pinhole lens (for testing the unit in regular lighting), a J-arm mount (used for mounting to a helmet or "skull crusher" headgear), as well as a weapon mount, for mounting the unit on a Picatinny rail either behind or in front of AR-height optics. It works great behind my Aimpoint PRO or Comp M4. It also works great in front of a scope that can adjust down to 1x.Get this very clean Gen 3 night vision unit in great condition for over $1,000 less than a new one would cost, or for the same as you would pay for a Gen 2 unit, if you want to think of it that way. If you have never used Gen 3 night vision, let's just say it blows Gen 1 and Gen 2 out of the water in every possible way... it's not even close. A unit like this gives you a massively unfair advantage in any low light situation.I would take $2200 OBO.I am willing to ship, with the buyer paying.Also, not interested in trading.

title: For Sale:  Colt Model 1878 Alaskan 45LC Revolver US 45 1902
postcontent: Up for sale is a very nice above average US marked Colt Model 1878 "ALASKAN" double or single action revolver. Also known as the 1902 Philippine Military DA model. Chambered in 45LC (.45 Colt), 6" barrel, blued finished, fixed front sight, large trigger guard, lanyard loop, and factory checkered hard rubber grips. Gun has great "CLEAR" markings. RAC inspectors marks throughout with "US" "1902" and "J.T.T" on the right side of the frame. Barrel is marked "45 COLT" with the one line Colt USA address on top. Pistol has all matching serial numbers including the load gate and cylinder. Manufactured in 1900. Gun is in superb above average condition with a great bore and strong working action on both single and double. Pistol shows lots of original blue in the protected areas along with accents of the fire blue on the trigger and hammer. Finish loss areas have turned a nice gray to brown patina with no signs of rust or pitting. Screws are all very nice with only the rear trigger guard screw having slot rounding. Grips are very nice as well with minimal checkering wear and mil handling. There is no damage or repairs on this revolver and is in very nice original unaltered condition. Most of these guns saw heavy use and are rarely found in the condition this one is! Nice historical US Military pistol.
